WEBVTT

00:10.880 --> 00:12.577
I need to be sure of you, Alfie.

00:12.708 --> 00:14.884
You've been
a little flighty recently.

00:15.015 --> 00:16.581
I need three seats
on next week's flight to Gotham.

00:16.712 --> 00:19.019
I hope America's worth
all this shite.

00:19.149 --> 00:21.499
The League have elected
a new prime minister.

00:21.630 --> 00:23.240
<i>Victor Aziz.</i>

00:23.371 --> 00:24.589
This new chap, Aziz,

00:24.720 --> 00:26.635
were he approached
confidentially,

00:26.765 --> 00:28.941
he might listen to reason.

00:29.072 --> 00:31.727
Do you speak for Harwood
and the Union or for yourself?

00:31.857 --> 00:33.033
I speak for the good
of the English people.

00:33.163 --> 00:35.861
Secret meetings
with the prime minister

00:35.992 --> 00:37.776
of the English League.

00:37.907 --> 00:39.430
I went to speak to him
on your behalf.

00:39.561 --> 00:40.692
Guards.

00:41.998 --> 00:43.565
I was trying to help you!

00:43.695 --> 00:44.609
Regarding Mrs. Gaunt--

00:44.740 --> 00:46.002
everyone I spoke to

00:46.133 --> 00:47.656
believes she's innocent
of the charges

00:47.786 --> 00:49.701
-against her.
-Do they?

00:56.404 --> 00:59.711
Take Lord Harwood away
and confine him to his quarters.

00:59.842 --> 01:00.799
I can explain.

01:03.150 --> 01:04.673
You haven't told him?

01:04.803 --> 01:05.891
Told him what?

01:06.022 --> 01:07.719
That you're pregnant.

01:07.850 --> 01:08.894
No, not yet.

01:09.025 --> 01:10.200
Don't blame you.

01:10.331 --> 01:11.375
He will freak the fuck out.

01:11.506 --> 01:13.595
Fuck.

01:13.725 --> 01:14.900
We have a job for you.

01:15.031 --> 01:16.902
We'll pay you very well.

01:17.033 --> 01:18.687
I don't need your money.

01:18.817 --> 01:19.949
Then we won't pay you
with money.

01:20.080 --> 01:22.169
We'll pay you with silence.

01:22.299 --> 01:23.779
What's that mean?

01:23.909 --> 01:26.347
You're meeting privately
with another man's wife.

01:26.477 --> 01:27.870
There's a lady involved.

01:28.000 --> 01:29.306
Mrs. Troy.

01:29.437 --> 01:30.916
<i>You fucking suicidal lunatic</i>

01:31.047 --> 01:32.309
<i>that you are.</i>

01:32.440 --> 01:33.310
The wife of Gully Troy?

01:33.441 --> 01:34.833
I gather the relevant husband

01:34.964 --> 01:36.705
is a man of strong feeling.

01:36.835 --> 01:38.968
Gully's dangerous.

01:39.099 --> 01:40.970
<i>Mad as a hatter.
The job we have</i>

01:41.101 --> 01:42.754
in mind won't take long.
It's a simple extraction.

01:42.885 --> 01:44.713
<i>One man.</i>

01:46.497 --> 01:47.585
Professor Fox, we have to go.

01:47.716 --> 01:49.761
Go, go, go, go, go, go!

01:51.154 --> 01:52.199
What have you got for us,
Professor?

01:52.329 --> 01:53.243
Film.

01:53.374 --> 01:54.853
Stormcloud.

01:54.984 --> 01:56.681
<i>The new version is at least</i>

01:56.812 --> 01:58.422
<i>five times more powerful
than projected.</i>

01:58.553 --> 02:00.772
They could kill
the entire population of London

02:00.903 --> 02:03.384
with a device the size
of a cigarette lighter.

02:03.514 --> 02:04.776
Someone's grassed us up.

02:04.907 --> 02:05.864
<i>Has he been acting strange
at all?</i>

02:05.995 --> 02:07.301
No.

02:07.431 --> 02:08.693
Don't take the chance.

02:08.824 --> 02:10.695
<i>Get out of there.</i>

02:10.826 --> 02:12.784
Thank you for letting me know.

02:40.812 --> 02:42.597
-Hello, Alfie.
-All right, boys.

03:18.633 --> 03:19.982
Melanie.

03:20.112 --> 03:21.418
Fuck's sake.

03:21.549 --> 03:23.028
You're lucky I didn't kill you.

03:23.159 --> 03:24.813
Mm. Well, that's me.

03:24.943 --> 03:26.162
Lucky.

03:26.293 --> 03:27.772
-What are you doing here?

03:27.903 --> 03:29.078
Should I not have come?

03:29.209 --> 03:30.732
You're taking a big risk.

03:30.862 --> 03:31.994
The risk's half the fun, no?

03:32.124 --> 03:33.300
No.

03:35.563 --> 03:37.608
Gully doesn't know anything.

03:37.739 --> 03:39.001
Stands to reason.

03:39.131 --> 03:40.698
Neither of us
would be walking around.

03:40.829 --> 03:42.439
Someone knows.

03:42.570 --> 03:44.615
-People know.
-Fuck people.

03:45.877 --> 03:47.705
Do you want to get found out?

03:47.836 --> 03:48.793
Do you have a death wish?

03:48.924 --> 03:50.882
Hmm.

03:51.013 --> 03:53.755
We're asking
the deep questions now.

03:53.885 --> 03:55.017
Okay.

03:58.063 --> 04:00.892
Why are you ashamed
of who you really are?

04:01.023 --> 04:02.981
Who's that then?

04:03.112 --> 04:05.201
Oh, you play
this hard-hearted tough guy,

04:05.332 --> 04:06.855
but, actually,
you're kind of a softie.

04:06.985 --> 04:08.726
Mm, feminine almost.

04:08.857 --> 04:09.988
-Get out.

04:10.119 --> 04:12.252
-You're a do-gooder.
-Mm.

04:12.382 --> 04:14.428
You only like me because
you think I need rescuing.

04:14.558 --> 04:16.430
You got me all wrong, love.

04:16.560 --> 04:18.388
-Heart of stone, me.
-Mm.

04:18.519 --> 04:19.911
See?

04:20.042 --> 04:21.739
Ashamed.

04:21.870 --> 04:23.306
Did you come here
for the banter or what?

04:23.437 --> 04:25.047
Mm-mmm.

04:35.579 --> 04:37.799
-Need.

04:39.409 --> 04:41.803
I appeal to you, my people,
at this time of great need.

04:41.933 --> 04:44.022
Uh, I...

04:44.153 --> 04:48.940
urge you, my people,
at this critical time.

04:49.071 --> 04:51.943
I urge you, my people,
at this critical time.

04:52.074 --> 04:53.554
...intercepted
before they reach the capital.

04:53.684 --> 04:56.687
<i>No supper for the League
tonight.</i>

04:56.818 --> 05:00.256
<i>We sign off with greetings
to our leader, Lord Harwood,</i>

05:00.387 --> 05:03.085
<i>who's taking some time off
at his country estate,</i>

05:03.215 --> 05:05.000
<i>recovering from a bout of the flu.</i>

05:05.130 --> 05:06.828
Bloody liars.

05:06.958 --> 05:08.046
<i>We wish him all the very best.</i>

05:08.177 --> 05:10.048
<i>Get well soon, Your Lordship.</i>

05:29.024 --> 05:30.852
It's beautiful, isn't it?

05:35.335 --> 05:37.162
-Sir...
-It's all right, old chap.

05:37.293 --> 05:38.947
Just gonna sit
under the old walnut tree.

05:39.077 --> 05:40.296
This is your perimeter, sir.

05:40.427 --> 05:42.124
Father planted it
on my seventh birthday.

05:42.254 --> 05:44.518
I'm sorry, sir.
You can't go any further.

05:44.648 --> 05:45.823
Don't be absurd.

05:45.954 --> 05:47.259
It's only ten feet away.

05:47.390 --> 05:48.739
Do I look
like I'm gonna run off?

05:48.870 --> 05:49.871
-Orders.

06:11.066 --> 06:12.067
You, Colonel Salt?

06:12.197 --> 06:14.025
-In charge?
-Colonel as was.

06:14.156 --> 06:15.375
"Sir John Salt" being
my current title.

06:15.505 --> 06:17.333
In charge
of the whole damn country?

06:17.464 --> 06:19.727
Yeah, it seems strange
to me, too, but there we are.

06:19.857 --> 06:22.120
-I shall do my best.
-What about the Union Council?

06:22.251 --> 06:24.166
An advisory body, sir.

06:24.296 --> 06:26.647
When the chancellor's
indisposed,

06:26.777 --> 06:28.692
the Union constitution
stipulates

06:28.823 --> 06:31.042
that his deputy administers
business until such time

06:31.173 --> 06:34.089
as the chancellor is fit
for duty again.

06:34.219 --> 06:36.221
Or, if he is unable to return,

06:36.352 --> 06:37.614
an election can be held.

06:37.745 --> 06:39.268
Ridiculous. But very well.

06:39.399 --> 06:41.792
You can start
by putting Harwood on trial.

06:43.794 --> 06:46.188
-Trial?
-Speedy trial for murder

06:46.318 --> 06:48.669
or commitment
to a lunatic asylum.

06:48.799 --> 06:51.149
-The Army won't settle for less.
-Nor should they.

06:52.716 --> 06:53.935
But a trial now?

06:55.327 --> 06:58.287
It would be a terrible blow
to the war effort.

06:58.418 --> 07:00.158
And the war's near won.

07:01.377 --> 07:02.987
Only London remains.

07:03.118 --> 07:05.207
A war won mostly by the Army
so far.

07:05.337 --> 07:07.252
We will win,

07:07.383 --> 07:09.907
with or without
your Raven Union militias.

07:10.038 --> 07:11.605
With or without Harwood.

07:11.735 --> 07:13.215
I'm sure you're right, General.

07:13.345 --> 07:15.957
So why talk of disunity
at this bright moment?

07:16.087 --> 07:17.828
If we simply bide our time

07:17.959 --> 07:20.570
and keep Harwood locked up
safe and quiet on his estate

07:20.701 --> 07:21.963
until victory is ours,

07:22.093 --> 07:24.226
-would that be such a crime?
-Mm.

07:24.356 --> 07:26.010
We need him alive and well
for now,

07:26.141 --> 07:27.534
smiling for the newsreels.

07:28.448 --> 07:30.711
Nobody need know
he's your prisoner.

07:30.841 --> 07:32.364
Perhaps you're right.

07:32.495 --> 07:35.411
And if,
as an absolute last resort,

07:35.542 --> 07:38.109
we were forced
to use Stormcloud...

07:40.372 --> 07:42.853
...it would be done
in Harwood's name.

07:42.984 --> 07:44.725
God forbid.

07:44.855 --> 07:45.900
Hmm?

07:46.030 --> 07:47.771
Oh, yes, indeed.

07:49.381 --> 07:50.861
God forbid.

07:53.124 --> 07:54.256
Now, in the meantime,

07:54.386 --> 07:55.257
I think it's best
we formulate a plan

07:55.387 --> 07:57.346
-in Harwood's absence.
-Yes, yes.

07:57.477 --> 07:59.957
I understand
the southern territories are...

08:11.099 --> 08:13.188
Sykes' Pain Supplies.

08:13.318 --> 08:14.885
Is that Bet?

08:15.016 --> 08:16.060
Bet Sykes?

08:16.191 --> 08:17.932
No, it's Peg, her sister.

08:18.062 --> 08:19.020
Who's this?

08:19.150 --> 08:21.718
I work for Raven HQ.

08:21.849 --> 08:23.328
I transfer Lord Harwood's calls.

08:23.459 --> 08:25.940
Oh, yes, love.

08:26.070 --> 08:28.029
Is anything wrong?

08:28.159 --> 08:31.075
<i>Yes, actually.</i>

08:31.206 --> 08:32.207
<i>There is something wrong.</i>

09:26.478 --> 09:27.871
The president and her people

09:28.002 --> 09:30.221
<i>have discussed your report
in depth.</i>

09:30.352 --> 09:32.223
<i>They've decided
we're gonna let this one ride.</i>

09:32.354 --> 09:34.312
You're doing nothing?

09:34.443 --> 09:36.532
-No action? <i>
-Plenty action.</i>

09:36.663 --> 09:38.186
<i>All but essential
U.S. government personnel</i>

09:38.316 --> 09:40.405
<i>are to be evacuated from London.</i>

09:40.536 --> 09:42.756
<i>By stages, as discreetly
as possible, of course.</i>

09:42.886 --> 09:44.366
And then what?

09:44.496 --> 09:46.150
<i>Well, this is
an internal dispute</i>

09:46.281 --> 09:48.065
<i>in a sovereign nation.</i>

09:48.196 --> 09:49.284
<i>None of our business.</i>

09:50.241 --> 09:52.374
A brand-new weapon
of mass destruction

09:52.504 --> 09:55.029
is likely gonna be used
on civilians.

09:55.159 --> 09:56.726
That's not America's business?

09:56.857 --> 09:59.033
<i>No.</i>

09:59.163 --> 10:00.425
Can we at least brief Prime
Minister Aziz on the situation?

10:00.556 --> 10:02.602
The League have no idea
what they're facing.

10:02.732 --> 10:04.908
-The people of London... <i>
-No, absolutely not.</i>

10:05.039 --> 10:07.389
<i>The League leadership
and the London public</i>

10:07.519 --> 10:09.347
<i>will find out about Stormcloud
soon enough.</i>

10:09.478 --> 10:11.262
<i>It's not our job to inform them.</i>

10:11.393 --> 10:12.786
<i>The U.S. government
doesn't officially know</i>

10:12.916 --> 10:14.091
<i>about Stormcloud,</i>

10:14.222 --> 10:16.093
<i>and we don't need to know.</i>

10:16.224 --> 10:17.834
<i>We need deniability.</i>

10:17.965 --> 10:19.401
But you do know.

10:19.531 --> 10:21.272
<i>I'll deny that.</i>

10:21.403 --> 10:22.926
-You...
-Ma'am, surely now is the time

10:23.057 --> 10:25.625
for the U.S. government
to intervene forcefully,

10:25.755 --> 10:28.497
to forbid the use of Stormcloud
under international laws.

10:28.628 --> 10:32.327
<i>If Stormcloud is used,</i>

10:32.457 --> 10:35.330
<i>it'll end the war
pretty damn quick, right?</i>

10:38.420 --> 10:41.118
Uh, well...

10:41.249 --> 10:43.294
Well, yes, I guess it would.

10:43.425 --> 10:47.037
<i>Well, your president thinks
ending wars quickly is good.</i>

10:51.172 --> 10:53.478
My God.

10:53.609 --> 10:57.047
You sons of bitches want them
to use Stormcloud?

10:57.178 --> 11:00.311
<i>Dr. Fox, you've been through
a harrowing experience.</i>

11:00.442 --> 11:03.358
<i>Emotional feelings
are only to be expected.</i>

11:03.488 --> 11:06.187
<i>You'll both be on the embassy
flight tomorrow, without fail.</i>

11:06.317 --> 11:07.841
<i>Now, until then,</i>

11:07.971 --> 11:09.190
<i>you speak to no one.</i>

11:10.452 --> 11:12.367
<i>Silence.</i>

11:12.497 --> 11:13.455
<i>Clear?</i>

11:13.585 --> 11:15.457
Clear, Chief.

11:15.587 --> 11:17.851
-Very clear.
-Wait a minute. You...

11:17.981 --> 11:20.244
You cut me off!

11:20.375 --> 11:22.290
I had so much more
to say to her!

11:22.420 --> 11:24.205
That is
precisely why I cut you off.

11:24.335 --> 11:26.337
I was doing you a favor.

11:28.296 --> 11:31.081
Don't do me any more favors.

11:31.212 --> 11:33.214
Once those people mark you down
as unreliable, you're out.

11:33.344 --> 11:35.303
I want out anyway.

11:35.433 --> 11:36.870
And you are "those people."

11:37.000 --> 11:39.133
Two fair points.

11:39.263 --> 11:42.223
And "those people" are fixing to
drop-drop a literal terror bomb

11:42.353 --> 11:44.094
on the city we're standing in.

11:44.225 --> 11:45.879
And those people want us to
run away without warning anyone.

11:46.009 --> 11:47.663
Again, fair points.

11:47.794 --> 11:48.446
I should've let you dig
a deeper hole for yourself.

11:48.577 --> 11:50.405
I apologize.

11:50.535 --> 11:53.538
How the heck can you be so calm
and complacent?

11:53.669 --> 11:55.192
Are you seriously gonna go along
with this shit?

11:55.323 --> 11:56.498
I'm just as mad as you are.

11:56.628 --> 11:57.934
We work
for coldhearted sons of bitches,

11:58.065 --> 11:59.370
and now they've crossed a line.

11:59.501 --> 12:00.241
There's no use
telling them that.

12:00.371 --> 12:01.416
They know what they are.

12:01.546 --> 12:02.330
You won't change their minds--

12:02.460 --> 12:04.375
you'll only irritate them.

12:04.506 --> 12:05.594
Better than saying
nothing at all.

12:05.725 --> 12:07.988
-I beg to differ.

12:08.118 --> 12:09.554
Someday, when you need
federal research money

12:09.685 --> 12:12.296
for some cockamamie invention,
you'll thank me.

12:17.345 --> 12:18.389
-Hello? <i>
-Martha?</i>

12:18.520 --> 12:20.217
Oh. Hi.

12:20.348 --> 12:22.350
I'm-I'm glad you rang.

12:22.480 --> 12:24.221
-We need to talk. <i>
-Yes, we do.</i>

12:24.352 --> 12:25.092
<i>As soon as possible.</i>

12:25.222 --> 12:26.920
Uh... Yes.

12:27.050 --> 12:29.357
Good. It's important.

12:29.487 --> 12:30.967
Yes, it is.

12:31.098 --> 12:32.577
What is it you're talking about?

12:32.708 --> 12:34.710
Well... what do <i>you</i> want
to talk about?

12:34.841 --> 12:37.539
Well, I don't want to say
over an open line.

12:37.669 --> 12:40.585
Okay, well... same.

12:40.716 --> 12:42.500
Let's say this evening
at your place?

12:42.631 --> 12:44.415
-Um...

12:44.546 --> 12:46.417
I'll be here.

12:46.548 --> 12:47.549
Good.

12:50.595 --> 12:52.946
Huh.

12:53.076 --> 12:54.295
-What? <i>
Huh.</i>

12:54.425 --> 12:55.557
-What? <i>
Just...</i>

12:55.687 --> 12:57.080
huh.

13:01.389 --> 13:03.391
He was acting kind of weird.

13:03.521 --> 13:04.566
So were you.

13:04.696 --> 13:06.524
No, thanks.

13:06.655 --> 13:07.525
Oh, right.

13:10.528 --> 13:11.529
Taxi!

13:14.097 --> 13:15.577
-I apologize.
-For what?

13:15.707 --> 13:17.666
For calling you
one of those people.

13:17.797 --> 13:19.363
I am one of those people.

13:19.494 --> 13:21.235
I need a drink.
Do you drink, Lucius?

13:21.365 --> 13:23.150
I will drink you
under the porch.

13:26.631 --> 13:28.546
Two quid? You're robbing me,
Mr. Applebaum.

13:28.677 --> 13:30.461
Robbing you? I'm killing myself.

13:30.592 --> 13:31.549
That's solid oak, that is.

13:31.680 --> 13:33.029
Oak shmoke.

13:33.160 --> 13:34.465
By next week, matchwood, maybe.

13:34.596 --> 13:36.554
You've been saying that
for years.

13:36.685 --> 13:37.381
-And now I'm right.

13:37.512 --> 13:38.774
That's a fiver, at least.

13:38.905 --> 13:41.690
Alfie boy,
talk sense to your mum.

13:41.821 --> 13:43.083
-They've got us surrounded.

13:43.213 --> 13:44.649
London might be burning
next week.

13:44.780 --> 13:46.956
-That right?
-Gonna kill all of us,

13:47.087 --> 13:48.305
those that aren't making

13:48.436 --> 13:50.090
-their lucky escape.

13:50.220 --> 13:51.439
And she wants five pounds
for that?

13:56.139 --> 13:57.358
Good morning, Alfie.

13:59.403 --> 14:00.970
All right, Gully.

14:02.015 --> 14:04.495
I'll be in the kitchen
if you need me, Alfie.

14:07.194 --> 14:09.283
Come back later, Mr. A.

14:09.413 --> 14:10.501
All right, mate.

14:13.548 --> 14:15.071
-I'd like to apologize

14:15.202 --> 14:17.378
for the way it all ended up
on the last job.

14:17.508 --> 14:20.685
Things got
a little bit, uh, minty.

14:20.816 --> 14:23.297
I've ironed the problem out
now though.

14:23.427 --> 14:25.212
Mm.

14:25.342 --> 14:27.997
So...

14:28.128 --> 14:30.260
you really are leaving then.

14:31.174 --> 14:32.436
Told you I was.

14:32.567 --> 14:34.003
Hmm.
I've got one last job for you.

14:34.134 --> 14:35.048
Real beauty.

14:35.178 --> 14:36.527
I'm in the air tomorrow.

14:38.181 --> 14:39.574
What's the hurry, Alfie?

14:39.704 --> 14:43.447
Huh? Airplanes leave every week.

14:43.578 --> 14:45.449
You'll find someone else.

14:45.580 --> 14:47.321
I don't want anybody else.

14:48.496 --> 14:49.627
I want you, Alfie.

14:52.500 --> 14:54.850
Let me tell you about the job,
at least.

14:54.981 --> 14:58.506
Your share would be ten grand,
minimum.

15:01.074 --> 15:03.685
You could have a tunnel
under Threadneedle Street.

15:03.815 --> 15:05.078
Makes no difference.

15:05.208 --> 15:06.296
I'm leaving tomorrow.

15:07.732 --> 15:10.083
You were just gonna, uh...

15:10.213 --> 15:11.867
disappear, were you?

15:11.998 --> 15:14.435
Without so much
as a word of farewell.

15:14.565 --> 15:16.480
There's been no time.

15:19.440 --> 15:23.357
Well, I'm glad we had this
chance to say goodbye at least.

15:24.401 --> 15:25.533
Yeah.

15:25.663 --> 15:27.578
Mm.

15:36.761 --> 15:39.025
Is there something
you're not telling me, Alfie?

15:39.155 --> 15:40.330
No.

15:41.592 --> 15:43.072
Oh, well,
there must be something.

15:43.203 --> 15:44.552
Must be.

15:44.682 --> 15:46.423
No.

15:49.209 --> 15:50.645
There is, isn't there?

15:52.212 --> 15:53.735
No.

15:53.865 --> 15:55.563
I beg, beg,

15:55.693 --> 15:57.565
mind you,

15:57.695 --> 15:59.915
a dear old comrade for help

16:00.046 --> 16:03.571
and he refuses me because
he has a flight to catch?

16:04.746 --> 16:06.487
Seems improbable to me.

16:06.617 --> 16:09.446
Fuck's sake, Gully.

16:09.577 --> 16:11.448
I'm going to America.

16:11.579 --> 16:13.581
The flight's booked.

16:13.711 --> 16:15.452
I got tickets with
seat numbers and everything.

16:16.540 --> 16:18.412
Mm.

16:19.543 --> 16:20.718
Right. Cheerio.

16:20.849 --> 16:22.590
Cheerio.

16:24.331 --> 16:26.507
You're breaking my heart, Alfie.

16:28.639 --> 16:30.424
You're breaking
my fucking heart.

16:55.275 --> 16:56.580
Ooh, look, love, new boys.

16:56.711 --> 16:58.104
-Passes, please.
-Passes?

16:58.234 --> 16:59.583
We live here.

16:59.714 --> 17:00.758
You've still
to show your passes.

17:00.889 --> 17:03.196
Cheeky monkey. Ignore 'em, Bet.

17:03.326 --> 17:04.806
-Passes, indeed.
-Wait a sec.

17:04.936 --> 17:07.330
Touch me
and I'll scream bloody murder.

17:07.461 --> 17:09.724
She will, you know.
Klaxon with tits, this one.

17:09.854 --> 17:11.595
I'm warning you.
Not a finger.

17:11.726 --> 17:13.293
What's all this then?

17:13.423 --> 17:15.295
-They'd not show their passes.
-Is that so?

17:15.425 --> 17:16.774
Oi!

17:26.697 --> 17:27.481
Hmm.

17:29.918 --> 17:31.615
Just leave it on the side,
ladies.

17:31.746 --> 17:33.052
Oh, my God.

17:33.182 --> 17:36.098
-Look at the state of you.
Girls!

17:36.229 --> 17:38.274
-How on earth did you get in?
-Well, never mind that.

17:38.405 --> 17:39.797
We've come to get you out.

17:39.928 --> 17:41.277
We've got a car and a driver
down the road.

17:41.408 --> 17:42.713
Well, that's very heroic of you,

17:42.844 --> 17:43.671
but how do you propose
to do that?

17:43.801 --> 17:44.976
That's the British Army outside.

17:45.107 --> 17:47.588
A dozen pimpled squaddies.
No trouble.

17:47.718 --> 17:48.850
Well, go and get
your toiletries,

17:48.980 --> 17:50.243
some clean underpants
and we'll be away.

17:50.373 --> 17:52.506
-I suppose you heard what I did.

17:52.636 --> 17:54.595
I lost my temper,

17:54.725 --> 17:55.857
killed a poor boy.

17:55.987 --> 17:57.946
-Beat him to death.
-Yeah, we heard.

17:58.077 --> 17:59.904
Could happen to anyone.

18:00.035 --> 18:01.950
I should have stayed
in Salford with you two.

18:02.081 --> 18:04.648
-I was happy there.
-I told you as much at the time.

18:04.779 --> 18:05.910
Now, by all means,
feel sorry for yourself,

18:06.041 --> 18:08.087
but we've just duffed up
several squaddies,

18:08.217 --> 18:11.090
-so we need to be away sharpish.
-No, I-I'm beaten.

18:11.220 --> 18:13.744
The Army will never forgive me.
Salt planned it all along.

18:13.875 --> 18:15.877
He removed my family
and my allies

18:16.007 --> 18:17.661
and then he led me
by the nose to ruin,

18:17.792 --> 18:19.881
like the foolish old goat I am.

18:20.011 --> 18:21.317
Salt?

18:21.448 --> 18:22.840
-That speccy plonker?
-I know.

18:22.971 --> 18:24.712
It's hard to credit, isn't it?

18:24.842 --> 18:26.975
My people came over
with the Conqueror.

18:27.106 --> 18:28.890
We fought at Poitiers,
Agincourt, Water-fucking-loo.

18:30.892 --> 18:32.328
And here I am,

18:32.459 --> 18:35.026
deposed and deceived
by a jumped-up grocer.

18:35.157 --> 18:37.159
He made himself indispensable
to me,

18:37.290 --> 18:39.770
and now he's done exactly the
same to the Army and the Union.

18:39.901 --> 18:41.990
And while he's ruling
in my name as my deputy,

18:42.121 --> 18:43.600
then no one dare touch him.

18:43.731 --> 18:44.949
Not if you stop him.

18:45.080 --> 18:48.127
The best way to stop him
is to die now.

18:48.257 --> 18:50.041
With me dead, he won't be able
to rule in my name.

18:50.172 --> 18:51.695
He won't last long
without that leverage.

18:51.826 --> 18:53.044
But then you'd be dead.

18:53.175 --> 18:54.394
So let's keep
our thinking hats on, eh?

18:54.524 --> 18:56.091
-Too right.
-No, good. You're right.

18:56.222 --> 18:57.701
I can't exactly kill myself,
can I?

18:57.832 --> 18:59.138
-Cardinal sin and all that.
-Correct.

18:59.268 --> 19:01.705
So let's be away
before someone raises the alarm.

19:03.316 --> 19:04.969
Lord Harwood,
the house is surrounded

19:05.100 --> 19:06.928
<i>by a battalion
of the 3rd Rutland Infantry.</i>

19:07.058 --> 19:08.886
<i>You cannot escape.</i>

19:09.017 --> 19:11.019
<i>I ask you to surrender yourself
and your accomplices</i>

19:11.150 --> 19:12.499
<i>without further violence.</i>

19:12.629 --> 19:14.109
Sorry, ladies.

19:14.240 --> 19:16.459
I seem to have led you
into a sad predicament.

19:16.590 --> 19:18.679
It's not your fault.
We came of our own accord.

19:18.809 --> 19:20.376
Mind you,
if you hadn't dithered...

19:20.507 --> 19:21.986
No point nagging him now, eh?

19:23.510 --> 19:25.033
How old are those sandwiches?

19:25.164 --> 19:27.688
Oh, they're jolly good.
You should help yourself.

19:27.818 --> 19:30.386
-I wasn't nagging him.
-You were.

19:30.517 --> 19:31.779
No, I was merely pointing out

19:31.909 --> 19:32.954
that if we'd left
five minutes earlier,

19:33.084 --> 19:34.390
we'd be
in a better position now.

19:34.521 --> 19:36.392
That's what nags do.

19:36.523 --> 19:37.915
They merely point things out.

19:38.046 --> 19:38.960
Clear.

19:39.090 --> 19:40.353
I'll secure the library.

19:40.483 --> 19:41.745
You there.

19:43.443 --> 19:45.053
You tell them for me.

19:45.184 --> 19:47.838
I don't want any more bloodshed,

19:47.969 --> 19:50.363
but I don't trust
you Army chaps.

19:50.493 --> 19:51.973
I'll surrender tomorrow.

19:52.103 --> 19:54.671
Tomorrow and not before.

19:54.802 --> 19:55.977
And only to Colonel Salt.

19:56.107 --> 19:57.935
Only to him.

19:58.066 --> 19:59.633
In person.

19:59.763 --> 20:00.982
Colonel Salt!

20:02.766 --> 20:03.985
Surrender?

20:04.115 --> 20:05.421
Yes.

20:05.552 --> 20:07.423
Well, I bought us some time.

20:07.554 --> 20:10.644
We can have
a-a splendid evening together.

20:10.774 --> 20:13.777
-Just like the old days.
-Lovely.

20:13.908 --> 20:15.866
Couldn't be better.

20:15.997 --> 20:17.694
She's being sarky now
'cause I called her a nag,

20:17.825 --> 20:18.913
but she is, isn't she?

20:19.043 --> 20:20.436
No, I am not.
-You are.

20:20.567 --> 20:21.742
No, I'm not.

20:21.872 --> 20:23.918
To me? Only to me?

20:24.048 --> 20:25.702
They were very specific
on that point, sir.

20:25.833 --> 20:27.226
Typical.

20:27.356 --> 20:29.967
Empty theatrics, Miss Dixon.
Empty theatrics.

20:30.098 --> 20:32.622
-Yes, sir.
-Damn the man!

20:36.147 --> 20:37.975
I'll have to go.

20:39.934 --> 20:42.066
We can't allow this to escalate.

20:42.197 --> 20:44.155
Tell them
I'll be there in the morning.

20:44.286 --> 20:47.158
Reiterate that he's not to be harmed.

20:47.289 --> 20:50.553
Not to be harmed
under any circumstances.

20:53.252 --> 20:54.731
Here we go, eh?!

20:57.343 --> 21:00.389
