Some losers.

26:12.962 --> 26:14.921
A little heavy on the gin,
my love?

26:16.923 --> 26:18.533
-I'm celebrating.
-Oh?

26:18.664 --> 26:21.188
Three winners in a row
at Sandown Park this afternoon.

26:21.318 --> 26:22.406
Oh. Brava.

26:22.537 --> 26:24.887
-Mm.

26:26.193 --> 26:28.108
You don't look very happy.

26:29.065 --> 26:31.459
Well, it's horse racing,
not Zen Buddhism.

26:31.590 --> 26:36.116
Mm, you're never very happy.
Not recently.

26:36.943 --> 26:39.380
It makes me wonder
if everything's quite, um,

26:39.510 --> 26:40.729
shipshape.

26:42.296 --> 26:43.427
-Shipshape?
-Mm.

26:43.558 --> 26:44.690
Why wouldn't it be?

26:44.820 --> 26:46.343
Well, quite.

26:46.474 --> 26:47.780
What could--
what could possibly be wrong?

26:47.910 --> 26:49.956
Everything is shipshape.

26:50.086 --> 26:51.740
Good.

26:51.871 --> 26:54.221
Just checking. Oh...

26:54.351 --> 26:57.050
I'll have a little splash.

27:01.620 --> 27:04.405
You haven't asked if
everything's all right with me.

27:04.535 --> 27:07.147
Is everything all right
with you?

27:07.277 --> 27:10.454
Well, uh, since you ask, uh...

27:10.585 --> 27:13.022
I-I'm feeling
a little sad today.

27:13.153 --> 27:15.372
Why is that?

27:15.503 --> 27:19.333
I went to see...

27:19.463 --> 27:20.987
Alfie.

27:21.117 --> 27:23.250
-Oh?
-Yeah.

27:23.380 --> 27:25.121
Tried to get him
on the next job,

27:25.252 --> 27:27.167
but he said no.

27:27.297 --> 27:29.430
Leaving for America, you know.

27:29.560 --> 27:31.650
Oh. That's a shame.

27:31.780 --> 27:34.348
But I expect you can manage
just fine without him,

27:34.478 --> 27:35.958
can't you?

27:39.396 --> 27:41.747
But, see, it's not just, uh...

27:41.877 --> 27:43.966
not just that.

27:45.011 --> 27:47.274
No, he-he seemed tense,

27:47.404 --> 27:49.711
nervous.

27:50.843 --> 27:54.063
It was almost as if he was...
scared of me.

27:56.022 --> 27:58.415
-Well, I expect he was.
-Mm.

27:58.546 --> 27:59.678
Lots of people
are scared of you.

28:00.635 --> 28:02.202
I have a theory.

28:02.332 --> 28:03.943
Mm?

28:04.073 --> 28:07.163
-Want to hear it?
-I can't stop you.

28:08.295 --> 28:11.515
Yeah, I think...

28:11.646 --> 28:14.301
Alfie was scared of me

28:14.431 --> 28:19.219
because he suspected
that I know the truth.

28:21.221 --> 28:22.483
What truth?

28:22.613 --> 28:24.398
Oh, come on.

28:24.528 --> 28:26.400
-What truth?
-You know.

28:26.530 --> 28:27.923
-I know what?
-The truth.

28:28.054 --> 28:30.839
The truth. The truth.
Gully, stop talking in riddles.

28:30.970 --> 28:32.232
Riddles? No.

28:33.973 --> 28:35.801
A joke...

28:35.931 --> 28:37.019
maybe.

28:45.985 --> 28:47.508
Melanie.

28:47.638 --> 28:49.902
I know.

28:50.032 --> 28:51.164
You know what?

28:51.294 --> 28:52.600
No.

28:52.731 --> 28:55.559
I want to hear you say it.

28:55.690 --> 28:58.432
Oh, come on. Say it.

28:58.562 --> 29:00.521
Just say it. Huh?

29:00.651 --> 29:02.915
-Say it. Tell me. Tell me.

29:03.045 --> 29:04.438
Tell me. Say it.

29:04.568 --> 29:05.700
-Say it!
-You want me to say

29:05.831 --> 29:08.877
that I fucked Alfie Pennyworth,
huh?

29:09.008 --> 29:11.140
Is that what you want?

29:15.014 --> 29:16.363
All right.

29:19.018 --> 29:20.933
-I fucked him.
-Oh.

29:21.063 --> 29:22.499
-And I loved it.
-Hmm.

29:22.630 --> 29:24.458
-Next time,

29:24.588 --> 29:26.286
you can watch if you like.

29:28.549 --> 29:31.334
A whore like you,
why wouldn't you fuck him?

29:31.465 --> 29:32.335
-Now get up!

29:36.731 --> 29:37.645
-Come here. Come here.

29:37.776 --> 29:40.387
Come here.

29:59.362 --> 30:01.103
-Come on. Come on.

30:01.234 --> 30:02.409
Come on.

30:08.067 --> 30:09.198
Over here.

30:29.523 --> 30:31.046
God! God!

30:31.177 --> 30:32.569
-Stop! Stop.

31:07.735 --> 31:09.868
Not that I care what you think,

31:09.998 --> 31:12.522
but do you think
I'm doing the right thing?

31:14.655 --> 31:17.397
Well, I'm glad
I can say yes for once,

31:17.527 --> 31:19.573
without a shadow of a doubt.

31:21.096 --> 31:22.576
Obviously.

31:25.013 --> 31:28.016
You're getting your mother
and yourself out of harm's way.

31:28.147 --> 31:30.192
Exactly.

31:31.541 --> 31:33.326
Stay here and fight?

31:33.456 --> 31:35.545
Why? What for?

31:35.676 --> 31:37.547
Can't hold back the tide.

31:37.678 --> 31:40.072
Can't be done.

31:40.202 --> 31:42.770
Isaac Newton sorted all that.

31:42.901 --> 31:44.728
Isaac Newton sorted what?

31:44.859 --> 31:48.471
Tides. Caused by the gravity
of the moon.

31:48.602 --> 31:49.864
I know how bloody tides work.

31:49.995 --> 31:53.041
I'm saying
you can't argue with gravity.

31:53.172 --> 31:54.216
Oh, really?

31:57.872 --> 31:59.700
Speak for yourself.

32:03.269 --> 32:05.706
Who are you talking to?

32:05.836 --> 32:07.447
Melanie.

32:07.577 --> 32:10.711
I was, um, thinking aloud.

32:12.495 --> 32:13.888
What happened?

32:14.019 --> 32:16.760
-Are you all right?
-Been better.

32:16.891 --> 32:18.545
-Eh.

32:20.373 --> 32:21.678
Come on.

32:32.646 --> 32:35.083
He said you seemed scared.

32:35.214 --> 32:38.173
Made him suspicious.

32:38.304 --> 32:41.611
That's it? That's all he has?

32:43.135 --> 32:44.571
Were you?

32:44.701 --> 32:46.573
Scared.

32:46.703 --> 32:49.141
No.

32:49.271 --> 32:51.447
Well, maybe a bit.

32:53.797 --> 32:57.758
I denied everything,
but he just-- he knew.

32:57.888 --> 33:01.457
And he attacked me
and strangled me.

33:01.588 --> 33:04.808
I hit him with a vase.

33:04.939 --> 33:08.116
I think he's hurt,
but I don't know.

33:08.247 --> 33:10.118
There was a lot of blood.

33:10.249 --> 33:12.512
I ran away.

33:12.642 --> 33:14.557
You don't know where he is now?

33:14.688 --> 33:16.516
No.

33:20.694 --> 33:23.001
Turns out you were wrong.

33:24.654 --> 33:26.743
I don't have a death wish.

33:26.874 --> 33:28.832
I was actually...

33:28.963 --> 33:30.921
very frightened.

33:31.052 --> 33:33.533
Well, there's
a silver lining then.

33:34.577 --> 33:36.536
No death wish.

33:37.798 --> 33:39.756
And you're safe here.

33:44.500 --> 33:48.591
As angry as he was, I could see
in his heart that he was glad.

33:49.940 --> 33:53.640
Now he can be his true self.

33:53.770 --> 33:57.731
He'll kill me.
I'm not safe anywhere.

34:00.342 --> 34:02.475
I'll handle Gully.

34:04.955 --> 34:07.262
No.

34:07.393 --> 34:11.223
No, you have a plane to catch.

34:11.353 --> 34:13.921
And you'd better be on it.

34:14.052 --> 34:16.663
Or he'll kill you, too.

34:23.104 --> 34:25.193
You'd better come to America
with me then.

34:28.283 --> 34:29.719
Sure.

34:29.850 --> 34:31.547
-Have you got a passport?
-Yes, but...

34:31.678 --> 34:33.114
You're sorted then.

34:33.245 --> 34:34.768
I've still got plenty of cash,
and that's all it takes

34:34.898 --> 34:35.899
-to get you there.
-No, it's a lot of money.

34:36.030 --> 34:38.380
Easy come, easy go.

34:41.818 --> 34:43.733
You...

34:43.864 --> 34:46.214
you would really do that?

34:46.345 --> 34:48.129
For me?

34:48.260 --> 34:50.218
I'm buying you a plane ticket.
I'm not offering marriage.

34:52.090 --> 34:53.569
Yeah, well, I'd have
to say no if you did.

34:53.700 --> 34:55.223
-Would you?
-Mm.

34:55.354 --> 34:56.790
You're not my type.

34:56.920 --> 34:59.619
-Mm. Too soft.

35:00.968 --> 35:02.535
You-You're not...

35:02.665 --> 35:05.233
you're not joking?

35:05.364 --> 35:06.887
America?

35:07.017 --> 35:09.455
What did I just say?

35:11.587 --> 35:14.895
Well, I'm going to America.

35:23.991 --> 35:25.253
-Sorry.

35:25.384 --> 35:26.776
No, kiss me.

35:54.021 --> 35:54.935
Martha?

35:56.589 --> 35:57.546
Martha.

35:59.069 --> 36:00.636
Martha!

36:01.898 --> 36:03.465
Martha.

36:08.775 --> 36:10.472
Good day, Miss Kane.

36:11.299 --> 36:13.083
-Sorry it's late.
-Late?

36:13.214 --> 36:14.824
Do you have any idea
what time it is?

36:14.955 --> 36:17.610
Yes. I have
an excellent internal clock.

36:17.740 --> 36:21.004
It is 1:35.

36:21.135 --> 36:22.397
Rhetorical question.

36:22.528 --> 36:24.269
Oh. I hate those.

36:24.399 --> 36:26.749
Martha.

36:26.880 --> 36:28.186
You have to get out of here
right now.

36:28.316 --> 36:30.144
-What are you talking about?
-Stormcloud.

36:30.275 --> 36:32.277
What about Stormcloud?
What is it?

36:32.407 --> 36:33.843
Chemical weapon.

36:33.974 --> 36:35.802
Very, very bad.

36:35.932 --> 36:37.586
They are going to use it
on London.

36:37.717 --> 36:40.067
And the U.S. government
is going to look the other way.

36:40.198 --> 36:41.677
They want the war over. They're
not gonna tell the League

36:41.808 --> 36:42.722
what they know.

36:42.852 --> 36:44.506
But you just told me.

36:44.637 --> 36:45.681
So you know I'm going straight
to Aziz with this.

36:45.812 --> 36:47.553
Well, I hope so.

36:47.683 --> 36:50.730
The best way to stop Stormcloud
is public exposure.

36:50.860 --> 36:52.775
If Aziz yells loud enough,

36:52.906 --> 36:54.864
the White House
can't feign ignorance.

36:54.995 --> 36:56.388
The president can't
openly support a war crime.

36:56.518 --> 36:57.867
She'll have to intervene.

36:57.998 --> 36:58.955
I'll go to Aziz first thing.

36:59.086 --> 37:01.828
Well, uh,

37:01.958 --> 37:03.438
don't tell him who told you.

37:03.569 --> 37:05.266
I think he'll know anyhow.

37:05.397 --> 37:07.877
Well, if anyone asks,
I'll deny telling you anything.

37:08.008 --> 37:09.009
Unless, of course,
I'm under oath. But I...

37:10.532 --> 37:11.620
I doubt it will come to that.

37:13.448 --> 37:14.754
Hmm.

37:18.932 --> 37:19.846
What?

37:21.587 --> 37:24.024
I'm... I'm just surprised.

37:24.154 --> 37:27.157
And glad.
You're doing the right thing.

37:27.288 --> 37:29.116
Well, I'm glad you're glad, but
I'm surprised you're surprised.

37:29.247 --> 37:31.074
Why would I not try to stop
a mass murder?

37:31.205 --> 37:34.382
I don't know. To... avoid
seeming unconventional?

37:34.513 --> 37:35.992
She's got your number.

37:36.123 --> 37:38.821
You know your bosses
will work out who talked.

37:38.952 --> 37:40.083
Deniability's all I need.

37:40.214 --> 37:41.824
Okay.

37:41.955 --> 37:42.912
Okay, you're denied.

37:43.043 --> 37:44.566
Martha, where's the aspirin?

37:45.524 --> 37:46.742
Hi.

37:46.873 --> 37:48.396
I'm Patricia.

37:48.527 --> 37:49.876
Who are you?

37:50.006 --> 37:50.877
Lucius.

37:51.007 --> 37:52.444
Oh.

37:52.574 --> 37:54.097
Say that again.

37:54.228 --> 37:56.056
-Lucius?

37:56.186 --> 37:57.884
You have got such
a lovely timbre

37:58.014 --> 37:59.102
-to your voice.

37:59.233 --> 38:01.714
Why is everyone so glum?

38:01.844 --> 38:02.889
And what are you doing here?

38:03.019 --> 38:04.717
My sister.

38:04.847 --> 38:07.197
Pat, focus.

38:07.328 --> 38:09.635
There may soon be
a chemical attack on London.

38:09.765 --> 38:12.333
We're booked on a U.S.
government flight leaving today.

38:12.464 --> 38:14.814
We're all getting on
that flight. Pat, no arguments.

38:14.944 --> 38:16.250
Oh. I'll be on it. Absolutely.

38:16.381 --> 38:19.122
I despise chemicals.
Don't you, Lucius?

38:19.253 --> 38:20.863
Just to be clear,
I'm not going anywhere.

38:20.994 --> 38:22.778
Of course not. That figures.

38:22.909 --> 38:24.302
You're not going?

38:24.432 --> 38:25.868
We can stop them.
We can stop Stormcloud.

38:25.999 --> 38:27.957
-Oh, please.
-We have to.

38:28.088 --> 38:29.307
Martha, you have to go.
What about...

38:29.437 --> 38:31.657
No! Come on, Patricia.
Let's make some coffee.

38:35.661 --> 38:37.489
-See what I have to deal with?

38:37.619 --> 38:39.142
-Uh-huh.

38:48.282 --> 38:51.111
Right. That'll be him.

38:51.241 --> 38:52.939
-About bloody time.

39:06.300 --> 39:07.519
There you are.

39:07.649 --> 39:09.912
We've been worried sick.

39:10.043 --> 39:11.784
Now, Mum,

39:11.914 --> 39:13.002
this is Melanie.

39:13.133 --> 39:15.135
Melanie, my mum.

39:15.265 --> 39:18.834
Very nice to meet you,
Mrs. Pennyworth.

39:18.965 --> 39:20.793
Long story.
She's coming with us.

39:20.923 --> 39:22.011
Mm.

39:52.085 --> 39:54.000
Be back in a minute.

39:59.266 --> 40:01.007
Mrs. P.

40:01.137 --> 40:02.791
Sit there.

40:04.663 --> 40:06.012
Hi.

40:08.144 --> 40:09.972
And, um,

40:10.103 --> 40:12.018
that covers everything, right?

40:12.148 --> 40:14.063
Yes, sir.

40:14.194 --> 40:16.022
Just a few questions
for English border control.

40:18.111 --> 40:20.200
Reason for departure?

40:20.330 --> 40:21.984
Reason?

40:22.115 --> 40:23.812
Why are you leaving England?

40:25.205 --> 40:26.554
Lots of reasons.

40:26.685 --> 40:28.817
Business or pleasure?

40:30.776 --> 40:32.908
Is it business or pleasure?

40:33.039 --> 40:36.303
Oh. Uh, business.

40:36.434 --> 40:38.827
Have you flown before,
Mrs. Pennyworth?

40:39.698 --> 40:40.960
No.

40:41.090 --> 40:42.135
It's a little scary at first,

40:42.265 --> 40:44.137
but then it's-it's quite fun.

40:45.878 --> 40:48.794
I expect you're
a very experienced traveler.

40:48.924 --> 40:50.099
I am.

40:51.231 --> 40:53.451
Like to keep moving, do you?

40:53.581 --> 40:55.191
Flight is now ready to board.

40:57.280 --> 40:59.152
Here's-here's Alfie back.

41:06.768 --> 41:08.770
Off we go then.

41:13.906 --> 41:15.864
All passengers will depart...

41:31.750 --> 41:32.881
What is it?

41:35.057 --> 41:37.016
I can't go.

41:42.412 --> 41:44.066
I can't go.

41:46.329 --> 41:48.244
Thank you, God.

41:50.116 --> 41:52.901
For fuck's sake, Alfie.

42:03.433 --> 42:06.219
I can't go, but you can.

42:06.349 --> 42:08.047
You have to go.

42:16.446 --> 42:18.927
Try and stop me.

42:21.321 --> 42:23.845
What changed your mind
so suddenly?

42:25.630 --> 42:28.241
Stuff that sounds stupid
if you say it out loud.

42:30.156 --> 42:31.505
This is my home.

42:31.636 --> 42:33.115
If that's not
worth fighting for,

42:33.246 --> 42:35.204
then what is worth fighting for?

42:39.208 --> 42:40.949
Yeah, it does sound stupid.

42:44.300 --> 42:47.086
We would have been good
together.

42:48.304 --> 42:51.003
-We would.

42:52.482 --> 42:55.485
But in the long run,
you'll be better off without me.

42:55.616 --> 42:57.400
Bit of independence
is just the ticket.

43:01.796 --> 43:03.581
Will you be okay?

43:05.844 --> 43:08.281
Mm. Mm.

43:08.411 --> 43:10.718
I will be fine.

43:10.849 --> 43:12.981
I always land on my feet.

43:14.853 --> 43:16.898
What about you?

43:17.899 --> 43:20.119
Don't worry about me.

43:20.249 --> 43:22.556
-I got feet, too.

43:22.687 --> 43:25.298
Passengers for Flight 011 to Gotham

43:25.428 --> 43:27.256
<i>proceed to immediate boarding.</i>

43:27.387 --> 43:29.345
<i>-That's immediate boarding.</i>

43:29.476 --> 43:31.391
-Hey, don't cry.

43:31.521 --> 43:32.958
No, I'm not.

43:33.872 --> 43:36.048
It's a good thing
that's happening.

43:37.223 --> 43:38.964
New life for you.

43:40.182 --> 43:41.923
Here you go.

43:50.410 --> 43:55.284
If you ever do get to America,
you look me up.

43:57.417 --> 43:59.114
I'll do that.

44:30.580 --> 44:32.321
Sorry.

44:40.242 --> 44:42.027
I know you.

44:44.377 --> 44:45.247
You do?

44:45.378 --> 44:47.510
I don't forget gorgeous.

44:47.641 --> 44:49.251
Oh, my God, look at you.

44:49.382 --> 44:52.341
I would drown kittens
for those hips.

44:52.472 --> 44:53.342
Patricia.

44:56.432 --> 44:58.260
Melanie.

44:58.391 --> 45:00.349
Fleeing from an angry lover,
huh?

45:00.480 --> 45:02.874
No, no, don't deny it.

45:03.004 --> 45:04.789
What else could it be?

45:04.919 --> 45:07.269
We'll sit together. You're gonna
tell me the whole sordid tale.

45:07.400 --> 45:08.488
Take my mind off the journey.

45:08.618 --> 45:10.708
Are you scared of flying?

45:10.838 --> 45:14.320
No, I love flying.
I don't like airplanes.

45:14.450 --> 45:15.974
My brother was supposed
to come with me,

45:16.104 --> 45:18.454
but he decided to stay
and be a fucking hero.

45:40.607 --> 45:42.522
You're not going?

45:42.652 --> 45:44.045
No.

45:44.176 --> 45:46.308
Really?

45:46.439 --> 45:48.484
After all the trouble you went
through to get there? Why?

45:49.703 --> 45:51.574
Changed my mind.

45:51.705 --> 45:53.794
That's funny.

45:53.925 --> 45:57.058
I can't see a comical side,
but I suppose there is one.

46:00.061 --> 46:02.237
Why aren't you going?

46:02.368 --> 46:04.152
Changed my mind.

46:05.023 --> 46:06.546
Hmm.

46:12.595 --> 46:14.597
You know, Alfred,

46:14.728 --> 46:16.643
I think this
could be the beginning

46:16.774 --> 46:18.732
-of a beautiful friendship.
I doubt it,

46:18.863 --> 46:21.430
-but you never know, do you?

46:45.628 --> 46:47.456
Fuck me.

46:49.110 --> 46:51.286
My thoughts exactly.

46:52.766 --> 46:54.246
Your government knows
about this?

46:54.376 --> 46:55.725
They'll deny it.

46:55.856 --> 46:57.466
They want the Union
to use Stormcloud

46:57.597 --> 46:59.773
without their knowledge
or permission.

46:59.904 --> 47:01.383
Of course. They just want
the damn war over.

47:01.514 --> 47:02.732
Can't blame them, really.

47:02.863 --> 47:03.951
If you present
the U.S. president

47:04.082 --> 47:06.040
with this evidence publicly,

47:06.171 --> 47:07.694
she'll have to intervene.

47:07.825 --> 47:09.304
She can't be seen to stand by
and do nothing.

47:09.435 --> 47:11.654
She can't do nothing.

47:11.785 --> 47:13.526
At the very least,
we'll buy some time.

47:13.656 --> 47:15.876
Thank you, gentlemen.
We owe you a great debt.

47:16.007 --> 47:18.618
I can't believe this was an easy
choice for either of you.

47:18.748 --> 47:20.968
On the contrary.
It was very easy.

47:21.099 --> 47:22.709
I'm thinking of med school.

47:22.840 --> 47:24.363
That's a really great idea.

47:24.493 --> 47:26.408
You'll make an excellent doctor.

47:26.539 --> 47:28.802
Oh, finally,
I get your approval.

47:28.933 --> 47:30.630
Guess I've been kind of hard
on you, huh?

47:30.760 --> 47:32.458
Kinda.

47:39.465 --> 47:41.684
My old friend.

47:43.556 --> 47:45.514
So happy to have you back
in the fold.

47:48.909 --> 47:51.999
I'm already sorry
I didn't get on that plane.

47:52.913 --> 47:55.089
And you're still
a conniving little bastard.

47:55.220 --> 47:57.483
-Mm. Fair cop, guv.
-Mm.

47:59.528 --> 48:00.616
I'm glad to be back, too,
though.

48:00.747 --> 48:02.183
Mm.

48:05.665 --> 48:07.623
-Mm.
-You two have history, huh?

48:09.625 --> 48:11.410
Yeah.

48:55.758 --> 48:58.587
Salt's here.

48:58.718 --> 49:01.503
You're really gonna surrender
to that wanker?

49:01.634 --> 49:04.158
Well, what else are we to do,
brainbox?

49:04.289 --> 49:05.464
I believe I have a better idea.

49:05.594 --> 49:07.074
Oh, yeah? Now? Suddenly?

49:07.205 --> 49:08.075
We kill him, right?

49:08.206 --> 49:10.469
I like it.

49:10.599 --> 49:12.688
No, he'll be well protected.

49:12.819 --> 49:14.777
I shall create a diversion,

49:14.908 --> 49:16.518
draw the soldiers
to the front of the house.

49:16.649 --> 49:19.565
Meanwhile,
you two leave by the back.

49:19.695 --> 49:21.697
You head for the woods,
beyond the garden.

49:21.828 --> 49:23.612
Should work,
if we time it right.

49:23.743 --> 49:25.788
-A distraction?
-Yeah. I'll surrender

49:25.919 --> 49:28.704
and then I'll faint
or-or have a fit or something.

49:28.835 --> 49:31.490
Then, if you can,

49:31.620 --> 49:34.145
you get a message
to Frances Gaunt.

49:34.275 --> 49:35.885
You send her my fondest love,

49:36.016 --> 49:38.105
and you tell her
how deeply sorry I am

49:38.236 --> 49:39.541
for wronging her so cruelly.

49:39.672 --> 49:42.370
But what about you?

49:42.501 --> 49:43.589
Dearest Peg,

49:43.719 --> 49:45.156
Bet,

49:45.286 --> 49:46.766
you trust me?

49:46.896 --> 49:49.987
So trust
that I'll do the right thing.

49:50.117 --> 49:52.554
The greatest gift
that you two can give me now

49:52.685 --> 49:54.600
is your continued survival.

50:00.823 --> 50:02.390
Right.

50:11.921 --> 50:13.619
Lord Harwood,

50:13.749 --> 50:15.925
John Salt here, as requested.

50:16.056 --> 50:18.624
I'm very sorry
we're in this situation.

50:19.755 --> 50:21.496
Let's talk.

50:37.338 --> 50:39.166
-Good morning, sir.
-Silence!

50:39.297 --> 50:40.559
Scum.

50:45.042 --> 50:48.567
Soldiers of the Raven Union.

50:50.395 --> 50:53.615
This man is a treacherous dog.

50:53.746 --> 50:56.879
And I speak to you
as your rightful leader.

50:57.010 --> 51:01.232
We are fighting an unjust
and unnecessary war,

51:01.362 --> 51:03.060
and we must stop.

51:03.190 --> 51:07.803
I order you to lay down
your arms immediately.

51:09.675 --> 51:10.589
I will count to three,

51:10.719 --> 51:13.026
and any man who disobeys

51:13.157 --> 51:17.552
will be committing mutiny
and sedition.

51:19.641 --> 51:20.599
No!

51:21.904 --> 51:24.429
-One!
-Do not fire!

51:25.647 --> 51:27.388
Two!

51:29.869 --> 51:31.523
-Do not fire!
-Three!

51:31.653 --> 51:32.611
-Onward!
-No!

51:37.224 --> 51:39.531
Get to the front of the house!
Shots fired!

